-- Tue Apr 15, 2014 12:48PM EDT
-- None



April 15 (Reuters) -  U.S. stocks dipped on Tuesday, as gains in Coca Cola and Johnson & Johnson after their quarterly earnings were offset by mixed economic data and a resumed slide in momentum shares. The Dow Jones industrial average <.DJI> was down 0.50 percent at 16,093.06, the S&P 500 <.SPX> was down 0.56 percent at 1,820.3 and the Nasdaq Composite <.IXIC> was down 1.55 percent at 3,960.223. [.N]

** THE COCA-COLA CO <KO.N>, $40.09, +3.51 pct The beverage giant reported better-than-expected quarterly revenue as strong sales in China more than offset a drop in Europe and flat volumes in North America. [ID:nL3N0N72YU]  ** FX ENERGY INC <FXEN.O>, $3.24, +16.36 pct The oil and gas explorer said it had drilled its second well at Poland's Permian basin and results of a drill stem test are expected in about a week. [ID:nPn2C2MPQ]  ** PEP BOYS-MANNY, MOE & JACK <PBY.N>, $10.25, -14.37 pct The auto parts retailer reported a 7 percent drop in fourth-quarter revenue and said weak pricing is expected to hit results in the next quarter as well. [ID:nBw6zMDXda]  **  NATIONAL BANK OF GREECE SA <NBG.N>, $4.06, -8.97 pct Shares of Greece's biggest lender continued to fall on Tuesday after Reuters reported that it is moving ahead with plans for a share offering to bolster its capital. The bank must plug a 2.18 billion euro ($3.03 billion) capital shortfall under the terms of the country's international bailout, two senior bankers familiar with the issue told Reuters on Monday.[ID: nL6N0N61VF]  ** PETROLEO BRASILEIRO PETROBRAS SA <PBR.N>, $13.11, -5.55 pct Brazil's state-run oil company's shares extended the fall in early afternoon, while Chief Executive Mary Grace Foster attended the Senate hearing to discuss the company's purchase of a Pasadena refinery in the United States. Petrobras on Tuesday defended its 2006 decision to buy the refinery against allegations it had dramatically overpaid. [ID:nL2N0N70TR]  ** BRINK'S CO <BCO.N>, $25.25, -11.62 pct The provider of armored vehicle transportation to banks said it would no longer use Venezuela's official exchange rate of 6.3 bolivars per U.S. dollar and has adopted the government's SICAD II floating rate of about 50 bolivars per U.S. dollar. Brink's said it expects to incur a first-quarter charge related to the writedown of substantially all of its bolivar-denominated net monetary assets as a result of the devaluation. [ID:nPnQ1Bz5]   ** VERSARTIS INC <VSAR.O>, $25.6, +4.23 pct   Analysts at at least four brokerages initiated coverage of the biotechnology company's stock with their highest ratings, saying the company's long-acting experimental drug to treat growth hormone deficiency could be a standard treatment if approved, replacing the current treatment of daily hormone injections.  The analysts said the drug, VRS-317, could capture a substantial share in the market for growth hormones, which is worth over $3 billion worldwide. "VRS-317 should dramatically reduce dosing frequency, resulting in improved compliance, boosting patient results and incentivizing continued treatment," Canaccord Genuity analyst John Newman wrote in a note to clients. [ID:nWNBB04408][ID:nWNBB0441J] [ID:nWNBB0441S] [ID:nWNBB0443G]  ** EAGLE BULK SHIPPING <EGLE.O>, $2.9, -8.81 pct A deadline for the drybulk shipper to reach an agreement to prevent a default on its $1.1 billion term loan ends Tuesday. Analysts say the company continues to face imminent Chapter 11 or restructuring risk.  ** FEDFIRST FINANCIAL CORP <FFCO.O>, $21.55, +7.43 pct CB Financial Services <CBFA.PK> said it would acquire Fedfirst Financial Corp in a $54.5 million deal. FedFirst stockholders can choose to receive $23 in cash or 1.1590 shares of CB common stock for each FedFirst share. [ID:nGNXVAHHFa]  ** PERMA-FIX ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICES INC <PESI.O> $4.5499, -7.90 pct The provider of nuclear and mixed-waste management services reported a surprise fourth-quarter loss due to delayed government spending. [ID:nMKW2w733a]  ** ZEBRA TECHNOLOGIES CORP <ZBRA.O>, $62.2275, -8.86 pct ** MOTOROLA SOLUTIONS INC <MSI.N>, $63.03, -1.18 pct Barcode printer maker Zebra Technologies said it would buy Motorola Solutions's enterprise business, which makes rugged mobile computers, tablets and barcode scanners, for $3.45 billion in cash. [ID:nL3N0N72O0]  ** INFOSYS LTD <INFY.N>, $51.59, -7.18 pct Staff left India's second largest IT services exporter <INFY.NS> at an unprecedented pace in the last quarter, worrying its management and raising investors' concerns about its ability to win lucrative contracts even as it posted a higher-than-expected net profit for the period. [ID:nL3N0N70T7]  ** AARON'S INC <AAN.N>, $28.79, -5.51 pct The rent-to-own furniture and electronics retailer rejected a $2.3 billion takeover offer from a major shareholder and instead acquired a retail credit financing firm for about $700 million. [ID:nL3N0N72SW]  ** NEWMONT MINING CORP <NEM.N>, $23.49, -3.77 pct ** AURICO GOLD INC, <AUQ.N>, $4.24, -3.42 pct ** ANGLOGOLD ASHANTI LTD <AU.N>, $17.39, -4.24 pct ** MCEWEN MINING INC <MUX.N>, $2.275, -4.41 pct ** GOLDCORP INC <GG.N>, $23.49, -3.13 pct ** ROYAL GOLD INC <RGLD.O>, $65.59, -3.07-3.06 pct ** IAMGOLD CORP <IAG.N>, $3.48, -4.13 pct ** ENDEAVOUR SILVER CORP <EXK.N>, $4.25, -3.85 pct Gold prices fell more than 2 percent on Tuesday as strength in the dollar following forecast-beating U.S. retail sales data pushed it through key chart levels while silver hit a 2-1/2 month low. Spot gold <XAU=> hit a low of $1,290.34 an ounce and was down 2.6 percent at $1,291.40 an ounce at 1246 GMT, on track for its biggest one-day drop since Oct. 1.  ** CHARLES SCHWAB CORP <SCHW.N>, $25.48, +0.71 pct The discount broker reported a higher-than-expected quarterly profit due to a rise in trading commissions and fees for managing client assets. [ID:nL3N0N73CC]  ** JOHNSON & JOHNSON <JNJ.N>, $98.54, +1.44 pct The diversified healthcare company reported quarterly earnings well above Wall Street expectations, as strong sales of new prescription drugs offset weak sales of consumer products, and slightly raised its full-year profit view. [ID:nL2N0N70FA]  ** PAYCOM SOFTWARE INC <PAYC.N>, $15.32, +2.13 pct Shares of Paycom, a maker of cloud-based human resources software, rose to $17.92 in their trading debut, above the IPO price of $15. The offering, which raised about $99.7 million, underscored strong debuts by cloud-based enterprise software companies in recent months. [ID: nGNXVAHJNa]   ** PUBLIC SERVICE ENTERPRISE GROUP INC <PEG.N>, Monday close$39.3, +1.25 pct premarket   Analysts at Jefferies raised their price target on the New Jersey-based utility's stock to $40 from $37.50 based on valuation.   ** RIVERBED TECHNOLOGY INC <RVBD.O>, $18.6199, -1.27 pct